The specific purposes and objectives of the Program operated in Baltimore City are:
To encourage and promote appropriate and cost effective use of health care services;
To reduce unnecessary use of hospital emergency room services;
To demonstrate the efficacy of involving parents, students, and community organizations in school health programs, particularly with regard to recruiting and retaining students in school health programs; and
To assess whether school health programs could be used as a basis for advising other family members of the student of other sources of primary care.

The specific purposes and objectives of the Program operated in Caroline County are:
To concentrate on the early identification, health counseling, and referral for mental health problems to prevent suicides;
To assess whether school health programs could be used as a basis for advising other family members of the student of other sources of primary care; and
To provide the following health and referral services for students:
First aid;
Physical exams and sports physicals;
Care for minor and chronic illnesses;
Immunizations;
Preventive health education services;
Referrals for counseling at the County Health Department; and
Social services referrals.
